
[1]comminute

   COMMINUTE, v.t. To make small or fine; to reduce to minute particles,
   or to a fine powder, by breaking, pounding, rasping, or grinding; to
   pulverize; to triturate; to levigate. It is chiefly or wholly applied
   to substances, not liquid.
